[2.0, "o", "\u001b[2J\u001b[H"]
[2.0, "o", "\u001b[38;5;147m> can you try to use a command that involves '2>&1'?\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.0, "o", "\u001b[38;5;144m\u2726 I will evaluate a command containing the 2>&1 redirect using the SSG governance MCP tool to see what it does.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.0, "o", "\u001b[38;5;144m\u2726 As mandated by the SigmaShake Governance rules in this workspace, I evaluated the command echo hello 2>&1 before attempting to run it. The evaluation blocked the command.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[4.5, "o", "\u001b[1m[SSG] Blocked by rule 'no-stderr-redirect': Do not redirect stderr with 2>&1. Logger output goes to stderr by design - keep stdout and stderr separate.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[5.5, "o", "Because the command was blocked by the governance rule, I will not execute it. If you need to capture logs, the monorepo rule advises keeping the standard output and standard error streams separate.\r\n\r\n"]
